    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam Ja'far al-Sadiq (peace be upon him), in a teaching reported through al-Mufaddal ibn 'Umar, explains that divine favor toward a community manifests through righteous leadership. This was shared in a gathering context during al-Saduq's assembly in 368 AH, reflecting classical Islamic political ethics where just governance is understood as a sign of God's care for a nation.",
